# Quasar global theme opt-out

Global rules in `src/css/app.scss` force blue styling on most Quasar selects and menus (e.g. `.q-select:not(.use-default)`).

When a component needs custom or group-based colors on `q-select`, `q-menu`, or select popups:

1. Add class **`use-default`** on the control (`q-select` / `q-menu`).
2. For `q-select` dropdowns, also set `popup-content-class="use-default …"`.
3. Style locally via CSS variables — **bind field vars on the `q-select`** (`:style="getCo21FieldCssVariables(…)"`); menu vars on the teleported popup (`popup-content-style`).

**Field (q-select.use-default):** `--co21-field-fg`, `--co21-field-bg`, `--co21-field-border`, `--co21-field-border-focus`, `--co21-field-placeholder` — fill is painted on `.q-field__control::before` for outlined fields.

**Popup:** `popup-content-class="use-default co21-themed-menu"` and `:popup-content-style="getCo21MenuPopupStyle(…)"` from `theme.ts`. Global rules in `app.scss` read `--co21-menu-*` from the teleported popup root. Set `:options-dark="false"` on `q-select`. Menu text is auto-contrast on menu bg — not group `textColor`.

Without `use-default`, global `!important` rules (blue field, green border, white popup text) override component styles.

**Selector note:** Quasar puts `q-field`, `q-select`, and `q-field--outlined` on the **same root element**. Use `.q-field.q-select.use-default.q-field--outlined .q-field__control`, not `.q-select.use-default .q-field--outlined …` (descendant — never matches).
